---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import NewsletterCTA from '../components/NewsletterCTA.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Boardroom Wire is forensic business analysis of AI companies and tech industry developments — Bloomberg-style depth, PE/banker lens, no hype."
>
  <main>
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-gold">About</p>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl text-cream md:text-6xl">
        Forensic analysis of the companies shaping the future.
      </h1>

      <div class="article-prose mt-12">
        <p>
          Boardroom Wire is a research publication and YouTube channel
          covering the business of AI and the broader tech industry — with
          the depth of a sell-side analyst report and the bite of a
          private-equity memo. Strategic breakdowns, not product reviews.
        </p>

        <h2>What this is</h2>
        <p>
          Most AI coverage stops at "this looks cool" or "this looks
          dangerous." We start where that coverage ends — with the
          numbers, the structure, and the strategic logic. Who's winning,
          who's being recapitalized in slow motion, what the data rooms
          look like, and what it all means for the next ten years of the
          industry.
        </p>

        <h2>Who's writing</h2>
        <p>
          Dakotah Radabaugh — eight-plus years in private equity tech
          sales, applied here to AI coverage. Background in selling into
          the firms that quietly shape the deals you read about three
          quarters later.
        </p>

        <h2>How to read it</h2>
        <p>
          Three formats:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Articles</strong> — short-to-medium research notes,
            usually 600–1,500 words. The verdict is in the lead paragraph.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Videos</strong> — long-form breakdowns on YouTube with
            the dashboards and transcript embedded here.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Research</strong> — primary-source dashboards and
            datasets, refreshed as new filings drop.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <NewsletterCTA />
</BaseLayout>
